adjectives.description: camphory (comparative more camphory, superlative most camphory)

entries.meaning: Smelling of camphor; having a smell resembling that of camphor.
examples: "Here are cigars—some of your old ones. I found them in a trunk of mine, inside a camel's-hair shawl. You said they would keep the moths out. Don't you remember?" Kate was very voluble just here. ¶ "They must be camphory."
